[990.55764, "o", "\u001b[4mUNIQ\u001b[24m(1)                        User Commands                        \u001b[4mUNIQ\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       uniq - report or omit repeated lines\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1muniq \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... [\u001b[4mINPUT\u001b[24m [\u001b[4mOUTPUT\u001b[24m]]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       Filter adjacent matching lines from INPUT (or standard input), writ‐\u001b[m\r\n       ing to OUTPUT (or standard output).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       With no options, matching lines are merged to the first occurrence.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Mandatory  arguments to long options are mandatory for short options\u001b[m\r\n       too.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-c\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--count\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              prefix lines by the number of occurrences\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-d\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--repeated\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page uniq(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[991.034281, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[991.034359, "o", "              only print duplicate lines, one for each group\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-D     \u001b[22mprint all duplicate lines\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m--all-repeated\u001b[22m[=\u001b[4mMETHOD\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n              like \u001b[1m-D\u001b[22m, but allow separating  groups  with  an  empty  line;\u001b[m\r\n              METHOD={none(default),prepend,separate}\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-f\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--skip-fields\u001b[22m=\u001b[4mN\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              avoid comparing the first N fields\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m--group\u001b[22m[=\u001b[4mMETHOD\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n              show  all  items,  separating  groups  with  an  empty  line;\u001b[m\r\n              METHOD={separate(default),prepend,append,both}\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-i\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--ignore-case\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              ignore differences in case when comparing\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-s\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--skip-chars\u001b[22m=\u001b[4mN\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              avoid comparing the first N characters\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page uniq(1) line 22 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[991.536029, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[991.536109, "o", "       \u001b[1m-u\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--unique\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              only print unique lines\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-z\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--zero-terminated\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              line delimiter is NUL, not newline\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-w\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--check-chars\u001b[22m=\u001b[4mN\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              compare no more than N characters in lines\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m--help \u001b[22mdisplay this help and exit\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m--version\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              output version information and exit\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       A field is a run  of  blanks  (usually  spaces  and/or  TABs),  then\u001b[m\r\n       non-blank characters.  Fields are skipped before chars.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       'uniq' does not detect repeated lines unless they are adjacent.  You\u001b[m\r\n       may want to sort the input first, or use 'sort \u001b[1m-u\u001b[22m' without 'uniq'.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mAUTHOR\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page uniq(1) line 43 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[991.567823, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[991.568075, "o", "       Written by Richard M. Stallman and David MacKenzie.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mREPORTING BUGS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       GNU coreutils online help: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/>\u001b[m\r\n       Report    any    translation    bugs   to   <https://translationpro‐\u001b[m\r\n       ject.org/team/>\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSEE ALSO\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mcomm\u001b[22m(1), \u001b[1mjoin\u001b[22m(1), \u001b[1msort\u001b[22m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Full documentation <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/uniq>\u001b[m\r\n       or available locally via: info '(coreutils) uniq invocation'\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Packaged by Debian (9.7-3)\u001b[m\r\n       Copyright © 2025 Free Software Foundation, Inc.\u001b[m\r\n       License GPLv3+: GNU GPL  version  3  or  later  <https://gnu.org/li‐\u001b[m\r\n       censes/gpl.html>.\u001b[m\r\n       This is free software: you are free to change and redistribute it.\u001b[m\r\n       There is NO WARRANTY, to the extent permitted by law.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\nGNU coreutils 9.7                June 2025                          \u001b[4mUNIQ\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page uniq(1) line 64 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
